# Test Plan – FinanceTracker Web Application

## Test Plan Title
FinanceTracker – M2 Feature Testing

## 1. Introduction

**Purpose / Executive Summary**

This test plan defines the strategy for validating the FinanceTracker website
The purpose of this page is to ensure that core features function correctly before each milestone 

## 2. Scope of Testing

### In Scope
- Login page works
- Goal creation and progress tracking
- Limit setting is correct
- Purchases and  remaining balance works
- Category overview display
- Navigation between pages
- Goal Bar progressing graph
- Database interaction
- Backend code function

### Out of Scope
- Full authentication database integration
- Security testing

## 3. Test Objectives

- Correct  login behavior for valid and invalid credentials
- Make sure users can create and update savings goals
- Category limits are correctly stored and updated
- Purchases reduce remaining budget amounts
- Warning messeages for certain input
- Ensure navigation links load correct pages
- SQLite database has correct data

## 4. Testing Approach

### Methodologies
- Manual Testing
- Incremental Testing during development

### Types of Testing
- Functional Testing
- Integration Testing

### Tools Used
- Manual Browser Testing
- Flask 


## 5. Test Schedule (To be determined)

| Phase | Start Date | End Date |

## 6. Test Environment
Environment
- Local Flask Development Server
- Render Deployment Environment

Test Data Sources
- Mock categories (Rent, Groceries, Entertainment)
- Sample purchase values
- Test goal values


## 6. Test Deliverables

- Test Plan Document
- Bug reports/issues
- Updated test results

## 7. Entry & Exit Criteria

### Entry Criteria
- Core features implemented
- Routes functional

### Exit Criteria
- User flow works
- Core features functional:
  - Login
  - Goal tracking
  - Budget management
  - Working navigation
  - Dashboard is an accurate representation of spending habits

